# Dotfiles

This repo manages Vim, Zsh, and related tooling configs. The `install.sh` script
creates symlinks into `$HOME` and sets up local templates.

## Install
```sh
./install.sh
```

Dry run (no filesystem changes):
```sh
./install.sh --dry-run
```

## Local files
- `~/.gitconfig.local` is created from `gitconfig.local.template` if missing.
- `~/.zshenv.hosts/HOSTNAME.zsh` is created from `zshenv/host-template.zsh` if missing.

## Managed files (symlinks)
- `.vimrc`, `.vim`
- `.zshenv`, `.zshrc`
- `.gitconfig`, `.gitignore.global`
- `.screenrc`, `.ctags`, `.ugrep`, `.globalrc`
